						<summary>

						

						<p>Pillar in the Sāhebu Bazaar.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Śaka 1055: 1133 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This is dated Śaka 1055 which may correspond to 1133 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This inscription records the gift of 55 sheep entrusted into the hands of Gāde-bōya, son of Pēri-śeṭṭi for a perpetual lamp to the deity Trikōṭīśvaradēva by Vāsi-nāyaka, son of Prōli (Brōli)-nāyaka on the occasion of <hi rend="italic">Uttarāyaṇa-saṅkrānti.</hi> The shepherd was required to measure out annually a <hi rend="italic">māna</hi> of ghee for the lamp.</p>						

						<p>Published in <hi rend="italic">S.I.I.,</hi> Vol. X, No. 94.</p>						

						</summary>
